analysis: The documents consist of executive orders issued by President Truman, addressing various aspects of government operations, including public health service, termination of authorities, civilian defense, Puerto Rico, civil service rules, housing in D.C., military cemeteries, war production, selective service, and federal employee safety. The documents reflect Truman's efforts to manage the transition from wartime to peacetime, address specific issues related to government functions, and ensure the well-being of federal employees.
title: Governmental Management Directives
